================================================================================
Third-party dependencies
================================================================================

This software builds on third-party open-source components, each under its own
license (see each crate's own license metadata and the generated SBOM for the
authoritative, version-pinned list). Notable runtime dependencies include:

  - tokio, axum, tower         (MIT)            — async runtime / HTTP
  - reqwest, hyper             (MIT / Apache-2.0)— HTTP client, used for the
                                                   Streamable HTTP + legacy SSE
                                                   upstream transports
  - serde, serde_json          (MIT / Apache-2.0)— serialization
  - clap                       (MIT / Apache-2.0)— CLI parsing
  - sha2, hex                  (MIT / Apache-2.0)— audit-ledger hash chain
  - thiserror, anyhow          (MIT / Apache-2.0)— error handling
  - toml                       (MIT / Apache-2.0)— config parsing
  - async-trait, futures-util  (MIT / Apache-2.0)— async plumbing

Planned dependencies for later roadmap phases (not yet vendored): the official
MCP Rust SDK (`rmcp`), `wasmtime` (WASM sandbox, Phase 4), and an OAuth/JWKS
stack (Phase 2). When added, their attribution is reflected here and in the SBOM.

A complete, version-pinned dependency manifest with licenses is produced as a
CycloneDX SBOM at release time (see OSS-ROLLOUT.md §5–§6).
